sp.p:
And Hodge—






AIR.

                                          Hodge.



Well, well, ſay no more;

Sure you told me before;

I ſee the full length of my tether;

Do you think I'm a fool,

That I need go to ſchool▪


I can ſpell you and put you together.




A word to the wiſe

Will always ſuffice;

Addſniggers, go talk to your parrot;

I'm not ſuch an elf,

Tho' I ſay it myſelf,

But I know a ſheep's head from a carrot.
Exit.

My ſweet, pretty papa, your moſt obedient humble ſrvant;
hah, hah, hah! was ever ſo whimſical an accident!
Well, ſir, what do you think of this?

Get along, get along;
[driving in Lucinda before her]
you are a ſcandal to the name of Woodcock: but I was reſolved to find you out, for I have ſuſpected you a great while, though your father, ſilly man, will have you ſuch a poor innocent,

Then, ſir,
I am the happieſt man in the world;
I enquire no farther; here I fix the utmoſt limits of my hopes and happineſs.

Adds me, ſir, here are ſome of your neighbours come to viſit you, and I ſuppoſe to make up the company of your ſtatute ball;
yonder's muſic too, I ſee:
ſhall we enjoy ourſelves? If ſo, give me your hand.
